add jib file in pom.xml in all microservices and push it to hub using mvn clean pacakage -DskipTests
open gcloud cli
init
create project->enable Kubernetes for created project and cluster on Google cloud
check the connection on cli
create k8s folder in root of of your Microservice application
create pods i.e yml files for db and services ,connect services with db inside service.yml files
keep type as ClusterIp for internal ip secures,if Loadbalancer thn its external too
therefore keep all the services ClusterIp
CREATE INGRESS.yml file and alow only api gateway ,ingress is like security interpreter
you can also make api-gateway.yml as LoadBlancer but better use ingress
for windows use Kubectl ,and for mac use k for commands on gcloud cli
